name: 1,2-propanediol, 3-(2-methoxyphenoxy)-, 1-carbam
Reason: 1,2-propanediol has a melting point of around 50 degrees Celsius. The methoxyphenoxy group (–O–C(=O)–O–) adds approximately +20 degrees Celsius due to increased molecular weight and van der Waals forces. The carbamate group (1-carbam) adds approximately +20 degrees Celsius due to increased molecular weight and hydrogen bonding potential.
